public Card removeCard(int index)
Remove a card from the deck. After removal all index positions of trailing cards have shifted. Remember that indexing is zero-relative.

Parameters:
index - - index position of card to remove
Returns:
the card at the index position.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when index is out of range.

Parameters:

Returns:
the card removed.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the card is not in the deck.
